attributes.magic: ELF 64-bit LSB executable, x86-64, version 1 (SYSV), dynamically linked, interpreter /lib64/ld-linux-x86-64.so.2, for GNU/Linux 2.6.18, BuildID[sha1]=924f75d2d50cd659e5f304937dc8491b77caa81d, stripped

crowdsourced_ai_results.analysis: This binary is a Linux ransomware sample, likely a variant of LockBit or a similar family, given the internal string obfuscation and behavior. It exhibits classic ransomware traits: it traverses the filesystem, filters out critical system files and extensions (e.g., ntldr, .exe, .dll) to maintain OS stability, encrypts user data using the Libsodium library (Poly1305, BLAKE2b, Curve25519), appends a custom extension, and drops ransom notes named 'restore-my-files.txt'. It also employs anti-analysis techniques by using ptrace to detect debuggers and XOR-based obfuscation for its internal configuration and strings.
